body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

```verilog
module inner (i, o);
	input wire i;
	output wire o;

	parameter A = 1;
endmodule

module top (i, o);
	input wire i;
	output wire o;

	parameter A = 1;
	inner #(.A(A)) n (.i(i), .o(o));
endmodule
```

```
yosys -p "read_verilog test.v; chparam -list; write_json out.json"
```

## Actual behavior

The `chparam -list` part will produce the following;
```
top:
  A
inner:
  A
```

Which I believe means that Yosys seems to understand that there are parameters associated with these modules. (BTW -- Any chance `chparam -list` could also include the default value?)

In the output JSON, the **cell** `n` will have;
```json
      "cells": {
        "n": {
          "hide_name": 0,
          "type": "inner",
          "parameters": {
            "A": 1
          },
          "attributes": {
            "module_not_derived": 1,
```

Which I think means that Yosys understands that `1` value was used for the `A` parameter in the `n` cell.

However, there is no `parameter` property on `modules` output or any indication that the modules have parameters in any way.

## Expected behavior

It would be nice if Yosys included a list of parameters (and even better if that list included the default values).

## Version Info

`Yosys 0.8+319 (git sha1 2c7e2541)`

